{
  "stem": "3346.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The only one that was-- that was alive was-- because my mother had half brothers-- brothers and sisters, and half brothers and half sisters.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because my grandmother-- my-- my grandfather-- I've never known him, but I understand that he was the only Jewish senator ever to be in Poland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean the Jews weren't very liked in Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was very wealthy and very powerful.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Konigsberg.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That is what my mother told me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That is not first-hand.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He died long before I was born.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] But he was-- everybody knew him-- that I do know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And well, there we were, trying to find someone, and the only person we found was one of my mother's-- my mother's oldest half-- half sister, [NON-ENGLISH], who also lost all her-- for her-- her two daughters, and her son, and her husband.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and the others, well, we knew that one wasn't-- my mother's younger brother-- youngest brother, who was an engineer, died in the-- in the ghetto in Poland-- but not in Warsaw-- but not in the ghetto-- in the uprising.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He worked in a factory.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one of the stones broke and cut his face.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he died from the infection during the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we knew about him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But all the sisters and all that-- we heard that some of them were on those ships that the Germans said they were sending to Israel and then sank.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But nobody has ever appeared afterwards, so I assume that they all died.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some were on what we called Polish papers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because my mother heard-- had sisters-in-law-- two sisters-in-law and one sister who were blond, and blue-eyed, and very Polish looking.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they may have passed as-- but obviously they didn't, because they never appeared again.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
